{"id":1218,"date":"2022-02-19T10:58:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-19T10:58:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1218"},"modified":"2022-02-18T11:01:14","modified_gmt":"2022-02-18T11:01:14","slug":"modify-the-system-bootloader","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1218","title":{"rendered":"Modify the system bootloader"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>What even is a system bootloader? Weill It\u2019s part of the Linux boot process which you can see on the bellow picture. It&#8217;s place in what&#8217;s called GRUB, and its role is to execute kernel of the OS.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"300\" height=\"285\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-138.png?resize=300%2C285&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1219\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-138.png?w=300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-138.png?resize=24%2C24&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-138.png?resize=36%2C34&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-138.png?resize=48%2C46&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To modify this system bootloader, you have to interrupt the boot process. But we can see bootloader file context even when the system is UP. To do that simply go to \/boot\/grub2 and open a textfile called grub.cfg<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/boot\/grub2\/grub.cfg<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"92\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=640%2C92&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1220\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?w=790&amp;ssl=1 790w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=300%2C43&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=768%2C110&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-139.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But as you can see, this won&#8217;t serve to you anything. But it&#8217;s still nice to know how it looks\/works and I can show you a thing or two about what we are gonna work with.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"quiet\"><strong>quiet<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"66\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=640%2C66&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1221\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?w=776&amp;ssl=1 776w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=300%2C31&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=768%2C79&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-140.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This serves the simple purpose of hiding the bootloader process from display while booting. In the different words, it triggers what called a<a href=\"https:\/\/wiki.archlinux.org\/title\/silent_boot\"> <strong>Silent boot<\/strong><\/a>. It&#8217;s really a matter of preference. I for example like to see it, but for some reason it&#8217;s default hidden.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"grubby\"><strong>grubby<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>To change configuration within the OS we use a tool called &#8220;grubby&#8221;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"566\" height=\"53\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?resize=566%2C53&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1224\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?w=566&amp;ssl=1 566w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?resize=300%2C28&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-143.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>To list a default kernel<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">grubby --default-kernel <\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"586\" height=\"78\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?resize=586%2C78&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1222\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?w=586&amp;ssl=1 586w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?resize=300%2C40&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-141.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 586px) 100vw, 586px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>To list information about this default kernel <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">grubby --info=DEFAULT<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"104\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?resize=640%2C104&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1223\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?w=741&amp;ssl=1 741w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?resize=300%2C49&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-142.png?resize=48%2C8&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>You can see the index is 0 which is pretty much just it&#8217;s ID number, which we can change to pick a different default kernel for example.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change the default kernel <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">grubby --set-default-index=1<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"51\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=640%2C51&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1225\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?w=784&amp;ssl=1 784w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=300%2C24&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=768%2C62&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=36%2C3&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-144.png?resize=48%2C4&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Removing quiet with grubby <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">grubby --remove-args=quiet --update-kernel=DEFAULT<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"132\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?resize=640%2C132&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1226\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?w=737&amp;ssl=1 737w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?resize=300%2C62&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-145.png?resize=48%2C10&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And as you can see the quiet argument is gone and we should see the boot process on the next boot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"how-to-interrupt-a-boot-process\">How to interrupt a boot process <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least is how do we even interrupt this boot process? Well simply reboot your OS and wait for a GRUB menu to appear which look like this<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"594\" height=\"357\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?resize=594%2C357&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1229\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?w=594&amp;ssl=1 594w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?resize=300%2C180&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?resize=24%2C14&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?resize=36%2C22&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-147.png?resize=48%2C29&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And then simply press &#8220;e&#8221; for edit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>NOTE: To make this easier, we can change the timeout settings in which you can type a letter &#8220;e&#8221;. TO do this, we need to edit \/etc\/default\/grub textfile.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">vi \/etc\/default\/grub<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"143\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?resize=640%2C143&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1227\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?w=718&amp;ssl=1 718w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?resize=300%2C67&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?resize=36%2C8&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-146.png?resize=48%2C11&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>And rewrite the timeout=5 to something like timeout=10.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"modifying-the-bootloader-on-the-boot\">Modifying the bootloader on the boot<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you interrupt the boot process in the grub menu with pressing e, you should see something like this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"595\" height=\"136\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?resize=595%2C136&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1230\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?w=595&amp;ssl=1 595w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?resize=300%2C69&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?resize=36%2C8&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-148.png?resize=48%2C11&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Which is pretty much the same thing I showed you before. We&#8217;ve also worked with this in previous posts, like in changing the forgotten root password post, so if you are interested you can check those out.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>What even is a system bootloader? Weill It\u2019s part of the Linux boot process which [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1174,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[313,331,444,323,445,220],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/rhsa-Deploy-configure-and-maintain-systems-1.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1218"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=1218"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1218\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1231,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1218\/revisions\/1231"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/1174"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=1218"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=1218"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=1218"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}